                <mxCell id="9qp1rgAnBwMAJgA7jmng-38" value="&lt;h1 style=&quot;margin-top: 0px;&quot;&gt;Understandings&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Transport Layer -- Establishes and maintains the connection with the MCP server/client and sends the content over the network. Does not care about intepreting the bytes&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Protocl Layer -- Converts the raw data to a structured response/request and will match responses to the original request using unique ID&#39;s it is also reponsbile for validation error reporting and routing. Should provide a good abstracted API for the client to interact with&lt;/p&gt;" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1">
